f post-transfusion infection, together with the potential to further increase the level of security from infection through the inactivation of blood components.The text also describes the major diagnostic systems and organizational models that modern technology provides us with a correct immunohematological diagnosis and an appropriate trasfusional therapy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBloodxTransfusion. 4aTransfusional Medicine. 4aTransfusional process. 4apatient safety. 7aMEDICAL / Health Risk Assessment.2bisacsh  aTransfusional Medicine, Patient Safety, Immunohaematology, Transfusion, Blood Donation.1 aVeronesi, Arianna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVicarioto, Maria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Medicine and Life Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023849508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Medicine and Life Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637915oZDB-23-GML0 cprintz978311028697740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028707340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110287073423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110287073.jpg  a978-3-11-023849-5  DGBA Backlist Medicine and Life Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GMLc2000d2014